{{for|Native American burial grounds in general|Mound builder (people)}} {{Infobox NRHP | name =Indian Burial Ground | nrhp_type = | image = | caption = | nearest_city= [[Charlestown, Rhode Island]] | coordinates = {{coord|41|23|48|N|71|38|0|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Rhode Island#USA | architect= | architecture= | added = April 28, 1970 | area = {{convert|0.1|acre}} | governing_body = Private | refnum = 70000005<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
The '''Indian Burial Ground''' is a historic [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]] [[cemetery]] on Narrow Lane in [[Charlestown, Rhode Island]]. Now part of a larger municipal park, the small ({{convert|0.1|acre|ha|adj=on}}) cemetery is believed to have been the burying ground for leaders of the [[Narragansett people|Narragansett]] and [[Niantic people|Niantic]] tribes. It is now fenced off by an iron post and rail fence, erected in the late 19th century.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url=http://www.preservation.ri.gov/pdfs_zips_downloads/national_pdfs/charlestown/char_narrow-lane_indian-burial-ground.pdf|title=NRHP nomination for Indian Burial Ground|publisher=Rhode Island Preservation|accessdate=2014-07-27}}</ref>
The cemetery was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1970.<ref name="nris"/>
